         <abstract>
            <p>The Auslander-Reiten quiver of a finite-dimensional associative algebra A encodes information about the indecomposable finite-dimensional representations of A and their homomorphisms. A component of the Auslander-Reiten quiver is called preprojective if it does not admit oriented cycles and each of its modules can be shifted into a projective module using the Auslander-Reiten translation. Preprojective components play an important role in the present research on algebras of finite and tame representation type. We present an algorithm which detects all preprojective components of a given algebra.</p>
          </abstract>
